external_knowledge:
- An adjustment in this context refers to any change or revision made to a pension record; 
- Total pension amount represents the total awarded pension for each employee; 
- Contributions refer to the amount of money paid towards a pension plan;
- The average pension amount is calculated across all employees within a plan.

sql:
SELECT AVG(adjustment_amount) AS average_adjustment
FROM pension_adjustments
WHERE adjustment_type = 'cost of living';

SELECT type
FROM retirement_events
WHERE type = 'retirement';

SELECT employee_id, SUM(amount) AS total_contributions
FROM pension_contributions
GROUP BY employee_id;

SELECT adjustment_amount, description
FROM pension_adjustments
WHERE adjustment_date LIKE '2022%';

